UnitRedemptionManager::constructor
├── when vaultManager is zero address
│   └── it reverts with RedemptionManager_ZeroAddress
└── when vaultManager is valid
    ├── it sets vaultManager
    ├── it sets lpusd from vaultManager
    └── it sets lastDecayTimestamp to block.timestamp


UnitRedemptionManager::redeem
├── when lpusdAmount is zero
│   └── it reverts with RedemptionManager_ZeroAmount
├── when users array is empty
│   └── it reverts with RedemptionManager_InsufficientVaults
├── when vault has zero debt
│   └── it reverts with RedemptionManager_VaultHasNoDebt
├── when hints not sorted ascending
│   └── it reverts with RedemptionManager_NotSortedByAscendingCR
├── when hints exhausted before full amount
│   └── it reverts with RedemptionManager_InsufficientVaults
├── when single vault covers full amount
│   ├── it calls redeemFromVault with correct debt and net collateral
│   ├── it spikes baseRate proportionally
│   ├── it updates lastDecayTimestamp to block.timestamp
│   ├── it emits Redeemed with correct parameters
│   └── it emits BaseRateUpdated with new baseRate
├── when partial vault redemption
│   └── it redeems available debt and leaves remainder in vault
└── when multiple vaults needed ascending CR
    ├── it redeems from lowest CR vault first
    └── it accumulates collateral correctly across vaults


UnitRedemptionManager::getEffectiveFeeRate
├── when baseRate is zero and no time elapsed
│   └── it returns MIN_FEE_BPS (50)
├── when baseRate plus min fee is below max
│   └── it returns baseRate plus MIN_FEE_BPS
└── when baseRate plus min fee exceeds max
    └── it returns MAX_FEE_BPS (1000)


UnitRedemptionManager::baseRateDecay
├── when no time elapsed
│   └── it returns baseRate unchanged
├── when 720 minutes elapsed
│   └── it returns approximately half the original baseRate
└── when more than max decay minutes elapsed
    └── it returns zero
